CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1963, pg. 1 reads: "Over 2,000 Join UNPC in Massive Pittsburgh Walk - Pretty Evelyn Stroud (flowered dress), employee of a local banking firm, took advantage of her lunch hour to join the pickets as they marched around the Duquesne Light Company Building on Monday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Evelyn Stroud wearing geometric patterned dress, and men, including one wearing suit and arm band reading, "Let's March," marching around Duquesne Light Company building, Downtown
